author: Wesley Sinor | wsinor@al.com
title: Auburn the underdog in road trip to Arkansas
text:
Auburn the underdog in road trip to Arkansas Gus Malzahn Bret Bielema Gus Malzahn and Bret Bielema shake hands after the game. Auburn vs Arkansas on Saturday, Nov. 2, 2013 in Fayetteville, AR Todd Van Emst (Todd J. Van Emst) Comments 
Auburn has opened as a 4-point underdog to Arkansas for Saturday's game in Fayetteville, according to VegasInsider.com . 
Auburn has been favored in five of its six games this season and has just one win against the spread -- Thursday's victory over Kentucky . 
The Tigers (4-2, 1-2 SEC) and Razorbacks (2-4, 1-2) are set to kickoff at 11 a.m. Saturday on the SEC Network. Auburn holds a 13-10-1 edge over Arkansas in the all-time series and is riding a two-game winning streak.
